g.text: Air pressure plays an important role in bee behavior and
foraging efficiency. Bees are highly sensitive to changes in
atmospheric pressure, often reducing their activity before
storms or periods of low pressure. A sudden drop in
pressure signals incoming bad weather, prompting bees to
stay close to the hive and avoid getting caught in rain or
strong winds. High and stable pressure, on the other hand,
encourages active foraging, as it usually brings clear and
calm conditions. Additionally, since air pressure decreases
with altitude, measuring it allows us to estimate the height at
